Interface SharedData

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    LanguageProcessorInterface, ResponseBuilderInterface
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LanguageProcessor, ResponseBuilder, ResponseSelector, ResponseTemplate

    public interface SharedData
    This interface has no methods, it's only purpose is to contain a pointer to the shared data structures so that they can be accessed by any class that implements this interface.
    Author:
    Yasha

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static KeyWordList masterKeys
      The master list of all the recognized key words.
      static java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> memTable
      The Memory Table, this is used to store data from user input for future use or reference.
      static HashTable responses
      The Hash-table data structure containing pointers to all of the response templates.

    • Field Detail

      • masterKeys

        static final KeyWordList masterKeys
        The master list of all the recognized key words.

      • memTable

        static final java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> memTable
        The Memory Table, this is used to store data from user input for future use or reference. This is a dictionary data structure used to store previous user input. For example, the key may be “Name” and the value “John Doe”. When the question “What is your name?” Is asked, the response would then be parsed and stored in the memTable.

      • responses

        static final HashTable responses
        The Hash-table data structure containing pointers to all of the response templates. They will have an entry in each bucket corresponding to each of their keywords.
